  "text": "The SharedInformer factory implementation in kubernetes/kubernetes lives under staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/ (the staging area for the client-go module). The architecture has three layers: (1) **Informer registration** \u2014 `informers/factory.go` defines `sharedInformerFactory` which implements `SharedInformerFactory`, with `InformerFor()` registering per-type informers and `Start()` launching them; `informers/generic.go` provides the `GenericInformer` wrapper; `internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` defines the `NewInformerFunc` type. (2) **List-watch mechanism** \u2014 `tools/cache/reflector.go` implements the `Reflector` that calls `ListAndWatch()` to list and then watch resources from the API server; `tools/cache/listwatch.go` defines the `ListerWatcher` interface and `ListWatch` struct that wrap the actual API calls; `tools/cache/reflector_data_consistency_detector.go` validates watch data consistency. (3) **Local cache/store sync** \u2014 `tools/cache/shared_informer.go` contains `sharedIndexInformer` and `sharedProcessor` that bridge the reflector to event handlers; `tools/cache/controller.go` is the low-level controller that wires reflector to DeltaFIFO queue; `tools/cache/delta_fifo.go` implements the `DeltaFIFO` queue that buffers changes; `tools/cache/store.go` defines the `Store`/`Indexer` interfaces and `cache` struct; `tools/cache/index.go` defines `Indexer` and indexing functions; `tools/cache/thread_safe_store.go` provides the thread-safe map backing the store.",
